WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
Marcel is a French mouse. 

00:03.300 --> 00:06.500
He lives on a beautiful old boat in Paris. 

00:06.600- -> 00:09.700
His home is under the kitchen floor. 

00:09.800 --> 00:17.380
He likes books, restaurants and old films. 

00:17.480 --> 00:20.180
He likes the opera too.

00:20.280 --> 00:27.020
One evening in June, Marcel finishes a detective story. 

00:27.120 --> 00:31.220
Then he goes to have dinner with some friends. 

00:31.720 --> 00:35.220
They live in the metro station at the Louvre. 

00:35.320 --> 00:39.000
After dinner, Marcel waits at the station. 

00:39.100 --> 00:43.000
He sees two men standing next to him. 

00:43.100 --> 00:47.220
The tall one is reading a magazine. 

00:47.320 --> 01:03.280
Look, he says. Here she is, opera star Miss Sarsadupa with her beautiful one million pound diamond ring, the white star.

01:03.380 --> 01:08.000
Her beautiful diamond ring. 

01:08.100 --> 01:12.000
The short man looks at the photo and laughs.

01:12.780 --> 01:16.500
Not after tonight, he says. 

01:16.600 --> 01:19.100
Marcel's mouth opens. 

01:19.200 --> 01:20.900
What? 

01:21.000 --> 01:26.100
Are the men going to steal Sarsadupa's diamond?

01:26.200 --> 01:31.220
He remembers an evening at the opera two weeks before.

01:31.220 --> 01:38.560
Sarsad's green dress, the music, the beautiful white star on her finger. 

01:39.660 --> 01:42.560
No, they can't steal it. 

01:46.660 --> 01:50.260
The train comes and the men get on. 

01:50.360 --> 01:54.860
Marcel pulls down his hat and follows them. 

01:54.960 --> 02:01.420
Half an hour later, he gets off again at Lamouette Station. 

02:01.520 --> 02:07.040
But there are hundreds of people and Marcel loses the two men. 

02:07.140 --> 02:10.240
Then he sees an old mouse. 

02:10.440 --> 02:17.500
Excuse me, he says. Do you know where Sarsadupa lives? 

02:17.600 --> 02:23.300
But when Marcel finds Sarsad's house, it's too late. 

02:24.180 --> 02:28.860
Yes, two men. She's telling the police on the telephone. 

02:28.950 --> 02:32.360
And they've got the white star. 

02:32.460 --> 02:37.580
At that moment, Marcel hears a motor start.
 
02:40.580 --> 02:44.140
Whoa, where's that coming from? He thinks. 

02:44.240 --> 02:48.000
Then he sees something at the end of the road.

02:48.100 --> 02:53.120
It's them. It's the thieves. And they're stealing a car. 

02:53.220 --> 02:57.820
He runs across Sarsad's garden and down the street. 

02:57.960 --> 03:04.180
He can see the car's number plate. It's near. Very near.

03:04.180 --> 03:10.800
Can I? He thinks. And he jumps. 

03:12.200 --> 03:16.100
Yes. Marcel sits on the number plate. 

03:16.200 --> 03:19.300
Good, he thinks.

03:19.860 --> 03:25.340
Then, after a second or two. What happens now? 

03:25.540 --> 03:30.340
The thieves drive across Paris very fast.

03:30.340 --> 03:33.160
Marcel can hear them in the car. 

03:33.260 --> 03:35.960
They're laughing and talking. 

03:36.000 --> 03:39.060
But Marcel is not laughing. 

03:39.160 --> 03:42.040
He is very, very angry. 

03:42.140 --> 03:47.640
After half an hour, the car stops next to a cafe. 

03:47.640 --> 03:51.040
It's late and the cafe is quiet. 

03:51.140 --> 03:54.260
In one corner is a woman. 

03:54.360 --> 03:57.260
The thieves sit at her table. 

03:57.360 --> 04:01.560
Marcel sits under the table and listens. 

04:01.660 --> 04:04.700
Have you got it? 

04:04.800 --> 04:07.100
The woman asks. 

04:07.200 --> 04:10.300
The tall man takes a box from his jacket. 

04:10.400 --> 04:15.260
Then he opens it. Look, he says. 

04:18.360 --> 04:21.160
The woman puts her hand to her mouth. 

04:21.260 --> 04:24.560
What a beautiful diamond. 

04:24.660 --> 04:28.500
This is it. Think, Marcel. 

04:28.660 --> 04:34.500
This is the moment. He bites the tall man's leg very hard.

04:34.500 --> 04:41.520
The tall man throws up his arms. 

04:41.620 --> 04:46.120
The box and the white star fly across the room. 

04:46.220 --> 04:49.520
What's that on the floor? 

04:49.720 --> 04:52.380
One waiter asks. 

04:52.480 --> 04:55.680
I don't know. Says another. 

04:55.780 --> 05:01.680
Is it? No. It can't be a diamond. 

05:01.780 --> 05:07.780
But before he can finish, Marcel runs across the room. 

05:07.880 --> 05:11.700
He puts the white star around his neck. 

05:12.500 --> 05:15.020
Then he runs to the door. 

05:15.120 --> 05:19.020
The thieves jump up and follow him. 

05:19.120 --> 05:23.220
Suddenly there are tables and chairs everywhere. 

05:23.340 --> 05:35.580
What's happening? An old man asks. I don't know his wife answers. 


05:35.680 --> 05:40.120
Who can understand young people these days? 

05:40.280 --> 05:46.020
Stop that mouse. Says the tall man. 

05:46.120 --> 05:50.920
Shut the door. Says the short one.

05:51.140 --> 05:53.700
But they're too late. 

05:53.800 --> 05:58.700
Marcel runs out of the cafe and doesn't look back. 

05:58.800 --> 06:02.700
After ten minutes, he stops. 

06:02.800 --> 06:05.260
There's nobody following him. 

06:05.360 --> 06:11.760
But where is he? Marcel looks right and left. 

06:11.860 --> 06:15.460
Then he sees a big white church. 

06:15.560 --> 06:23.160
Ah, the secret clerk. He thinks, now I know where I am. 

06:23.260 --> 06:28.160
It's late and there are no metro trains. 

06:28.460 --> 06:34.640
But Marcel isn't tired. He walks back to Zazar's house. 

06:34.740 --> 06:39.040
When he gets there, she's asleep in bed. 

06:39.140 --> 06:42.240
There's a table next to the window. 

06:42.340 --> 06:49.340
On it, Marcel can see lots of photographs, boxes and perfume bottles. 

06:49.580 --> 06:54.500
He runs across the floor and up one leg of the table.

06:55.140 --> 07:02.460
Now, he thinks, it's time to take off the white star. 

07:02.560 --> 07:09.360
In the morning, Zazar is going to be very, then Marcel stops. 

07:09.440 --> 07:15.240
Oh, no. He can't take the ring off. 

07:15.340 --> 07:20.540
He pulls and pulls. But nothing happens.

07:20.900 --> 07:28.260
Now what? He thinks. Then, of course, some soap. 

07:28.360 --> 07:32.860
He runs down the table leg and across the floor.

07:33.860 --> 07:40.120
Zazar's bathroom door is open. Marcel goes in and looks up. 

07:40.220 --> 07:43.320
A soap dish is above his head.

07:43.780 --> 07:47.900
Ten seconds later. He's sitting in it. 

07:47.980 --> 07:50.500
He puts some soap on his neck. 

07:50.600 --> 07:55.500
Then he closes his eyes and pulls again. 

07:55.600 --> 08:02.000
Yes! This time, the diamond ring comes off. 

08:02.100 --> 08:06.300
In the morning, Zazar finds the white star.

08:06.580 --> 08:11.440
It's on her bedroom table between two perfume bottles. 

08:11.540 --> 08:20.340
But I don't understand. She says, feeds don't bring things back. 

08:20.440 --> 08:25.120
How? She looks at the ring. 

08:25.220 --> 08:28.620
Then she looks at her face in the mirror.

08:28.980 --> 08:31.480
Then she looks at the ring again. 

08:31.580 --> 08:35.080
And why is there soap on it?

08:35.860 --> 08:42.820
She telephones the police. Next day, Zazar's story is in all the newspapers.

08:44.260 --> 08:48.900
Opera star's one million pound ring is safe, says one.

08:50.340 --> 08:56.980
Thieves bring back Jupon Diamond, says another. Now police ask why?

08:58.580 --> 09:02.840
And there are lots of photos of Zazar with the white star. 

09:02.940 --> 09:09.440
At home, at the Opera House, standing in front of the Eiffel Tower. 

09:09.540 --> 09:12.660
She looks very happy in all of them.

09:13.540 --> 09:19.540
Marcel's happy too. Back on his boat, he reads the newspaper stories.

09:20.980 --> 09:26.180
Then he looks in the mirror. There's a thin red line on his neck.

09:27.140 --> 09:37.780
Oh, what a night, he says. After that, he washes, has breakfast, and opens the window.

09:39.140 --> 09:46.420
It's a beautiful, warm morning. Marcel looks up at the blue sky and smiles.

09:46.420 --> 09:53.300
Now, he thinks, what's going to happen today?

